  "time_ut": 1659001066,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db6\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The Ambassador tells the Prime Minister about America's hope",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The American Ambassador to Sri Lanka Mrs. Julie Chang told Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena today (28) that it is the hope of the United States of America to see the political crisis resolved through democratic methods and to see a government formed in Sri Lanka where all parties come together.",
        "She said this when she met the Prime Minister at the Prime Minister's Office today (28) in the morning.",
        "The Prime Minister appreciated America's long-term and continuous diplomatic relations and trade relations with Sri Lanka.",
        "The Prime Minister said that the emergency financial assistance provided by the United States of America was a great strength to Sri Lanka at this critical time and stated that he expects further support for the development of the country's economic sector and energy sector.",
        "The Prime Minister requested the American Ambassador to increase direct investments in the private sector and provide technical and financial support to small and medium scale industries.",
        "The Prime Minister also requested to promote investment opportunities in the field of renewable energy.",
        "The Prime Minister stated that the government is committed to maintaining Sri Lanka's democracy and parliamentary system by further strengthening and protecting people's rights.",
        "The ambassador said that the United States of America is expected to provide further support in Sri Lanka's economic and political challenges.",
        "The ambassador mentioned that by creating a government of all parties, a window will be opened to receive the support of the International Monetary Fund, the United Nations and other institutional systems and to increase bilateral investments.",
        "She also said that the United States of America does not condone violence and non-democratic processes in any way."
      ],
